msgid "# Gem of Brightness _Wondrous item, uncommon_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/gem_of_brightness.md:8
msgid ""
"This prism has 50 charges. While you are holding it, you can use an action "
"to speak one of three command words to cause one of the following effects:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/gem_of_brightness.md:12
msgid ""
"The first command word causes the gem to shed bright light in a 30-foot "
"radius and dim light for an additional 30 feet. This effect doesn't expend a "
"charge. It lasts until you use a bonus action to repeat the command word or "
"until you use another function of the gem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/gem_of_brightness.md:12
msgid ""
"The second command word expends 1 charge and causes the gem to fire a "
"brilliant beam of light at one creature you can see within 60 feet of "
"you. The creature must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or "
"become blinded for 1 minute. The creature can repeat the saving throw at the "
"end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/gem_of_brightness.md:12
msgid ""
"The third command word expends 5 charges and causes the gem to flare with "
"blinding light in a 30- foot cone originating from it. Each creature in the "
"cone must make a saving throw as if struck by the beam created with the "
"second command word."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/gem_of_brightness.md:13
msgid ""
"When all of the gem's charges are expended, the gem becomes a nonmagical "
"jewel worth 50 gp."
msgstr ""
